To calculate the Debt to Asset Ratio as of the end of the reporting period (2024-01-31), we use the formula:

\[
\text{Debt to Asset Ratio} = \frac{\text{Total Liabilities}}{\text{Total Assets}}
\]

From the problem data for 2024-01-31:

- Total Assets = 14,066,175.95
- Total Current Liabilities = 2,736,025.72
- No other liabilities explicitly listed, so Total Liabilities = Total Current Liabilities = 2,736,025.72

Calculate:

\[
\text{Debt to Asset Ratio} = \frac{2,736,025.72}{14,066,175.95} \approx 0.1945
\]

Rounded to two decimal places: 0.19
